N:debugging
D:Debug code, runtime behavior, regressions, flaky failures, and code-adjacent incidents. Use when...
G:debugging regression root-cause flaky-tests reproduce isolate verify
U[6]:
  Reproduce and isolate a bug, regression, or flaky test
  Explain why code behaves differently than expected
  Narrow a failure to a specific input, environment, commit, or subsystem
  Design a minimal safe fix after the failing boundary is known
  Prove that a fix works with targeted regression coverage or reruns
  Investigate runtime behavior after the key logs, stack trace, or symptom are already available
S[6]{n,action}:
  1,Frame the failure before changing code
  2,Reproduce the bug on the smallest path
  3,Isolate the failing boundary
  4,Form one hypothesis and test it
  5,Implement the smallest root-cause fix
  6,Prove the fix and lock the regression
R[6]:
  Debugging is a reproduce isolate hypothesize verify loop, not random guessing
  Route raw symptom-first log triage to log-analysis
  Route broad perf work to performance-optimization
  Route test-policy work to testing-strategies
  Route diff judgment to code-review
  Add references and evals before any mutation loop
